  <itemBody>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <h4>The park has sent out a questionaire about Dracula's castle. About 100 children between ages 7 and 9 years old have answered. They were asked about how scary they thought the castle was, on a scale of 1 to 4. 4 is very scary, and 1 is not scary. <br/>
You have created 2 figures. They both show how scary the children thought the castle is. The park's employees have said how easy the figures are to read.</h4>
        <h6>Below each figure, you have to choose 2 answeres that you agree with. </h6>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-6">
        <choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_3" shuffle="true" maxChoices="2" minChoices="0" orientation="vertical">
          <prompt>
            <p>
              <img src="Forlystelsespark_kurvediagram.png" alt="Forlystelsespark_kurvediagram" width="100%"/>
            </p>
          </prompt>
          <simpleChoice identifier="scaleaxis" fixed="false" showHide="show">Christian: "The scale should be on the y-axis rather than the x-axis."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="similarcolors" fixed="false" showHide="show">Nasim: "The colors of the graphs look too similar."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="pie" fixed="false" showHide="show">André: "A pie chart would work better, since the sum will be 100"</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="scale" fixed="false" showHide="show">Lulu: "A line chart can make the reader think, that there are more than 4 points on the scale."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="zoom" fixed="false" showHide="show">Cal: "You cannot see all of the data points. The graph should be zoomed out".</simpleChoice>
        </choiceInteraction>
      </div>
      <div class="col-6">
        <choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_4" shuffle="true" maxChoices="2" minChoices="0" orientation="vertical">
          <prompt>
            <p>
              <img src="Forlystelsespark_søjlediagram.png" alt="Forlystelsespark_s jlediagram" width="100%"/>
            </p>
          </prompt>
          <simpleChoice identifier="notmany" fixed="false" showHide="show">Dorothy: There are not many people, who answered the questionaire. The diagram should therefore show the number of answers, not the percentage. Maybe the total number of participants should be shown."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="addto100" fixed="false" showHide="show">Caspar: "The percentages do not add up to 100."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="bluecolors" fixed="false" showHide="show">Ida: "If all of the colors were blue, but the color gradually got darker with larger numbers, it would be easier to understand."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="histogram" fixed="false" showHide="show">Carl: "Age groups are easier to show in a histogram."</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="middlecategory" fixed="false" showHide="show">Lindsey: "The scale is missing a middle category."</simpleChoice>
        </choiceInteraction>
      </div>
    </div>
  </itemBody>
